15:45.885 --> 15:47.385
Goofy teach tricks to Pluto.

15:47.420 --> 15:49.540
Mercedes is gonna
freak when she gets home.

15:49.555 --> 15:51.022
Hush. She's gonna fall
in love with him,

15:51.057 --> 15:53.491
just like I did. You have to
help me sell it to her so she,

15:53.526 --> 15:55.627
like, thinks he's really awesome
when she gets here, okay?

15:55.661 --> 15:58.096
Don't worry. I got your back.

15:58.130 --> 16:00.098
Sam? Did you
go back

16:00.132 --> 16:01.199
and adopt that dog?

16:01.233 --> 16:03.201
Uh... uh, hey.
I tried to stop him.

16:03.235 --> 16:04.502
Uh, baby, yeah.

16:04.537 --> 16:06.171
Sorry I didn't, uh, talk
to you about it first.

16:06.205 --> 16:07.439
It's just that when I saw

16:07.473 --> 16:09.107
McConaughey in his cage,
something inside me just clicked

16:09.141 --> 16:10.575
and I knew that we were meant
for each other.

16:10.609 --> 16:11.876
I blame Sarah McLachlan.

16:11.911 --> 16:14.079
I don't mean to be patronizing,

16:14.113 --> 16:17.282
but we have a kitchen full
of dead Chia Pets

16:17.316 --> 16:18.383
that you can't take care of.

16:18.417 --> 16:21.186
This is a living,
breathing creature.

16:21.220 --> 16:22.620
So is Artie,
and I take care of him.

16:22.621 --> 16:23.702
Hold up. Did you just...

16:23.723 --> 16:25.023
Look, hey, look, I know

16:25.057 --> 16:26.758
I can take care of him, okay?
I just...

16:26.792 --> 16:28.153
Give me a chance.
Look, look, look.

16:28.160 --> 16:30.462
Oh, McConaughey loves you.

16:30.496 --> 16:32.997
- He lo...
- Oh, oh, look at the face.

16:33.032 --> 16:35.900
- The pooch. He d... The face.
- Okay. Fine.

16:35.935 --> 16:40.372
If it's that important to you,
we will try it.

16:40.406 --> 16:41.973
Okay. She's gone. Let's go.

16:42.007 --> 16:44.242
- Did you pay the gas bill?
- Yeah.

16:44.276 --> 16:46.778
Uh, no.
Uh, I've...

16:46.812 --> 16:49.381
Artie was just
into this video game.

16:49.415 --> 16:51.983
Did you take out the recycling?

16:52.018 --> 16:54.586
Um, Artie was gonna do it
on his way out.

16:54.620 --> 16:55.954
Am I still here? Am I invisible?

16:57.523 --> 16:59.290
Hold up.

16:59.325 --> 17:01.092
Is that my faux-huahua?

17:01.127 --> 17:02.160
Uh...

17:06.132 --> 17:07.832
Oh, I did that.

17:07.867 --> 17:09.787
Okay, you better
clean this mess up.

17:09.801 --> 17:11.469
Okay, just because
McConaughey is cute,

17:11.503 --> 17:13.505
it doesn't mean...

17:20.179 --> 17:21.579
Oh, no.

17:21.614 --> 17:22.854
Oh, I know

17:22.882 --> 17:24.281
that that dog
is not eating my hair.

17:24.282 --> 17:26.017
I know

17:26.051 --> 17:28.586
that you did not let that dog
near my bedroom or my wardrobe

17:28.621 --> 17:30.622
or my makeup!

17:36.062 --> 17:37.662
I got to go. Um...
Sam!

17:37.697 --> 17:39.297
Can one of you guys
bring me Don't.

17:39.331 --> 17:40.632
Down the stairs? Don't you even speak.
Don't you even look

17:40.666 --> 17:42.033
I got you. like you're
about to speak to me.

17:42.068 --> 17:43.802
You just pack up that dog
and you take him back

17:43.836 --> 17:45.937
where you got him
or, so help me,

17:45.972 --> 17:47.872
I will go full-on Carcosa
on you.

17:56.916 --> 17:58.683
Easy.

17:58.718 --> 18:01.686
Okay.

18:06.289 --> 18:08.769
Oh, my God, is
that Rachel Berry,

18:08.794 --> 18:10.729
star of Broadway's
smash-hit musical

18:10.763 --> 18:12.831
I love her!

18:12.865 --> 18:15.400
I saw Funny Girl

18:15.434 --> 18:18.370
five times!
She is just so likeable!

18:18.404 --> 18:19.738
Oh!

18:19.772 --> 18:21.539
Ms. Berry,
what on earth are you doing

18:21.574 --> 18:22.941
walking all these
beautiful dogs?

18:22.975 --> 18:24.409
Well, someone has to.

18:24.443 --> 18:26.211
Did you know
that New York City shelters

18:26.245 --> 18:28.613
are the most overpopulated
in the state?

18:28.648 --> 18:31.883
What? No, I didn't know that.
That's such a shame.

18:31.917 --> 18:35.353
That's why I'm starting
my own dog rescue charity,

18:35.388 --> 18:37.856
Broadway Bitches.

18:38.924 --> 18:40.892
Okay. Wait,
just stay right there.

18:40.926 --> 18:43.194
At the, uh, Spotlight Diner.

18:49.969 --> 18:51.002
Okay.

18:51.037 --> 18:52.437
Oh, my God. Stay.

18:52.471 --> 18:54.339
Oh, my God.

18:55.608 --> 18:57.442
Oh, my God. Ah!

19:03.082 --> 19:04.322
Oh, my God.

19:15.971 --> 19:19.018
At least you're wearing underwear.
I got dragged four blocks

19:19.053 --> 19:20.620
and now I have to
pay for this dress

19:20.654 --> 19:22.155
and that man got
bit by a shih tzu.

19:22.189 --> 19:23.289
Seriously, is this a good idea?

19:23.323 --> 19:24.763
Because I feel like
I look worse now.

19:24.792 --> 19:26.826
No. Yes, this is
a good idea, okay?

19:26.860 --> 19:28.961
Um, everybody's talking
about your activism.

19:28.996 --> 19:31.631
And, in fact, out of the 500
Broadway Bitches Evites

19:31.665 --> 19:34.567
that I sent out this morning,
over half are confirmed.

19:34.601 --> 19:37.236
And I even have a reporter
from NYTheatreNews.com ready

19:37.271 --> 19:38.671
to do a piece on it.

19:38.706 --> 19:40.573
So just stick to the plan

19:40.607 --> 19:42.575
and don't go soft on me.

19:42.609 --> 19:45.511
Guys, I got good news.
I landed a role.

19:45.546 --> 19:47.480
"The Lexington Home

19:47.514 --> 19:49.615
for Retired Performers
presents Peter Pan"?

19:49.650 --> 19:50.583
And I'm Peter!

19:50.617 --> 19:51.617
They needed an
emergency replacement

19:51.652 --> 19:52.952
because the woman

19:52.986 --> 19:55.960
playing him dropped... out.

19:55.994 --> 19:57.227
Possibly be serious.

19:57.262 --> 20:00.898
I am, actually,
and I'm very excited about it.

20:00.932 --> 20:03.667
Opening night is Monday,
and I'd love to have you.

20:03.702 --> 20:05.336
No, sorry, can't make it.

20:05.370 --> 20:07.605
As much as I would love
to watch Homocchio

20:07.639 --> 20:09.873
and the Geriatric Puppets
put on a depressing

20:09.908 --> 20:13.310
sub-community theatre show,
Rachel's event is that night.

20:13.345 --> 20:14.845
Well, that shouldn't be
a problem

20:14.879 --> 20:16.313
because the show starts at 4:00.

20:16.348 --> 20:19.383
I'm sorry, Kurt. Santana has
me doing all these photo ops

20:19.417 --> 20:21.919
and interviews, and my
reputation is at stake here.

20:21.953 --> 20:23.887
Seriously, you know,
I could lose jobs

20:23.922 --> 20:25.356
if I don't clean this up.

20:25.390 --> 20:28.959
I bend over backwards for you
every time you need something.

20:28.994 --> 20:32.263
Well, I need you now
so please support me in this.

20:32.297 --> 20:35.633
I am doing something good
for the animals.

20:35.667 --> 20:37.034
No, you're doing it
for yourself.

20:37.068 --> 20:39.436
You treat me exactly like
the world treats those dogs...

20:39.471 --> 20:41.105
you just cast me aside.

20:41.139 --> 20:42.339
Well, I'm done being a friend

20:42.340 --> 20:44.220
only when it's convenient
for you.

20:46.069 --> 20:48.989
Mercedes doesn't want me
to get rid of the dog, okay?

20:49.014 --> 20:50.781
She just wants him
to stop tearing everything up.

20:50.815 --> 20:53.183
You seriously think
you can train that dog?

20:53.218 --> 20:55.119
I had to teach you
how to use Velcro.

20:55.153 --> 20:57.655
Okay, yeah, well, Velcro's hard.
It's like black magic.

20:57.689 --> 21:01.358
But, look, I can do this, okay?
Doggies crave discipline.

21:01.393 --> 21:04.562
We'll just run him through
the Doggy Gauntlet of Doom...

21:04.596 --> 21:06.564
it's a working title,
don't judge me...

21:06.598 --> 21:09.233
and then once Mercedes gets home
tonight, he'll be groomed,

21:09.267 --> 21:11.235
trained and ready
to melt her heart

21:11.269 --> 21:14.605
with those big, beautiful puppy
dog eyes that he gets from me.

21:14.639 --> 21:17.007
- Let's do it.
- All right, good.

