23:26.905 --> 23:30.007
Peter, we killed a giant bird
while you were gone.

23:32.711 --> 23:34.979
If I get down,
I'm not getting back up.

23:35.013 --> 23:36.714
Oh, we look ridiculous!

23:36.748 --> 23:38.382
What were we thinking when

23:38.416 --> 23:39.750
we chose to do Peter Pan?

23:39.784 --> 23:41.418
Well, we wanted
to show our families

23:41.453 --> 23:43.154
that we were still
energetic and young.

23:43.188 --> 23:44.355
Right, Freddie?

23:46.358 --> 23:48.859
But you guys are still
energetic and young.

23:48.894 --> 23:51.729
You know, if you want to seem
young, you got to feel young.

23:51.763 --> 23:53.130
I don't know about all of that.

23:53.165 --> 23:55.299
I was thinking
of changing up the music.

23:55.333 --> 23:56.667
You know, maybe updating it
a little bit.

23:56.701 --> 23:58.269
I still think that we should do

23:58.303 --> 24:00.938
The Importance
of Being Earnest.

24:00.972 --> 24:03.541
Ever since you were a question
on Jeopardy!,

24:03.575 --> 24:05.676
you have been
such a know-it-all.

24:06.878 --> 24:08.879
Maggie, flowers came for you.

24:08.914 --> 24:10.181
Oh.

24:13.452 --> 24:15.953
Oh, they're from
my daughter, Clara!

24:15.987 --> 24:19.089
She's a defense
attorney. "Mom,

24:19.124 --> 24:22.493
"sorry I have
to miss opening night.

24:22.527 --> 24:24.929
I have to be in Reno
for a deposition."

24:27.866 --> 24:29.834
Oh.

24:29.868 --> 24:33.270
She is so thoughtful.

24:33.305 --> 24:35.539
She spoils me.

24:37.509 --> 24:39.477
Oh, that's too bad.

24:39.511 --> 24:41.912
I know how important
Clara is to her.

24:41.947 --> 24:43.614
She talks about her constantly.

24:43.648 --> 24:46.008
All about their lunches, and
their late night phone calls,

24:46.017 --> 24:47.218
and their double dates.

24:47.252 --> 24:49.220
Except none of it's real.

24:49.254 --> 24:51.122
Those flowers aren't
from her daughter.

24:51.156 --> 24:52.957
Maggie sends herself flowers

24:52.991 --> 24:54.959
once a week
to keep up appearances.

24:54.993 --> 24:57.461
Clara hasn't been here in years.

25:05.337 --> 25:08.239
You are shredding my last nerve.

25:08.273 --> 25:10.741
Before you say anything else,
you should know

25:10.776 --> 25:13.344
that Artie and I tamed the beast
that is McConaughey.

25:13.378 --> 25:14.545
He's not barking,

25:14.579 --> 25:16.881
he's been off his leash
for the last few hours,

25:16.915 --> 25:18.783
but didn't poop anywhere
he wasn't supposed to,

25:18.817 --> 25:20.985
and he didn't eat any
of your weird, strange,

25:21.019 --> 25:22.987
Indian hair.

25:23.021 --> 25:26.123
All of that is great,

25:26.158 --> 25:27.992
Sam, but we talked about this,

25:28.026 --> 25:30.728
and we both agreed,
we can't take care of a dog.

25:30.762 --> 25:31.996
Really? Because
it looks like

25:32.030 --> 25:33.764
I'm doing a pretty good
job of it right now.

25:33.799 --> 25:35.332
For the moment.

25:35.367 --> 25:38.669
But what's gonna happen when
you have, like, a 20-hour shoot,

25:38.703 --> 25:41.772
and you can't walk McConaughey,
or-or put out his food?

25:41.807 --> 25:44.341
I don't know. I thought
maybe you could help.

25:44.376 --> 25:48.112
Well, I would, and I could, but
what happens when I go on tour?

25:48.146 --> 25:51.282
Uh, we could get a dog-sitter.
I don't know.

25:51.316 --> 25:52.483
Who's gonna call the sitter?

25:52.517 --> 25:55.052
Who's gonna make sure
that they have a key to get in?

25:55.087 --> 25:56.520
Who's gonna pay them?

25:56.555 --> 25:58.389
I am, and you know what else
I've been thinking about?

25:58.423 --> 26:00.424
You going on tour, and me
being in this brownstone,

26:00.459 --> 26:03.160
all alone
and wanting some company.

26:04.663 --> 26:06.430
You know, last time I checked,

26:06.465 --> 26:08.265
New York's a pretty lonely town.

26:08.300 --> 26:09.934
Is that what
this is really about?

26:09.968 --> 26:11.936
Maybe.

26:11.970 --> 26:13.804
Partly, yes.

26:13.839 --> 26:15.039
But if we're being honest,

26:15.073 --> 26:16.373
I think it's also about

26:16.408 --> 26:18.275
when I suggested
we take McConaughey home,

26:18.310 --> 26:21.078
you couldn't even imagine me
being able to take care of him,

26:21.113 --> 26:22.993
okay, and that's just...
that's just crap, okay.

26:23.014 --> 26:25.249
It's like you're looking at me
like I'm a boy and not a man.

26:25.283 --> 26:27.418
- Sam...
- Look, I took care of

26:27.452 --> 26:29.019
my whole family
when they had nothing, okay.

26:29.054 --> 26:30.988
When they were as poor
and as homeless as McConaughey.

26:31.022 --> 26:32.189
I made sure they ate,

26:32.224 --> 26:33.691
I made sure
they had a roof over their head,

26:33.725 --> 26:34.885
I made sure my little brother

26:34.893 --> 26:36.093
and sister got
to school on time.

26:36.128 --> 26:37.294
Me, Sam, the slacker.

26:37.329 --> 26:38.796
- Oh, Sam, I... I know.
- But, yeah, yeah, yeah.

26:38.830 --> 26:41.165
I know... I know
that I forget about

26:41.199 --> 26:42.533
appointments sometimes,

26:42.567 --> 26:44.402
and I leave my clothes
around the apartment,

26:44.436 --> 26:45.903
and I get distracted
playing video games,

26:45.937 --> 26:47.371
but that doesn't mean
I'm a joke.

26:47.406 --> 26:49.707
I never called you a joke.

26:49.741 --> 26:52.376
Mercedes, look, I...
I want to marry you eventually,

26:52.411 --> 26:54.612
when we're ready, and I
want to have a family

26:54.646 --> 26:55.846
with a house and a yard
and kids and stuff,

26:55.881 --> 26:57.381
but that's only gonna happen

26:57.416 --> 26:59.417
if you start taking me
seriously, and that starts with

26:59.451 --> 27:02.753
me proving to you that I can
take care of McConaughey.

27:02.788 --> 27:06.924
You-you did, and, uh, I'm giving
you your props for that.

27:06.958 --> 27:08.826
Okay, great.
But I...

27:08.860 --> 27:11.395
I still don't think
that you should keep him.

27:11.430 --> 27:12.530
Why not?

27:13.899 --> 27:15.366
Because it's not good for him,

27:15.400 --> 27:17.234
Sam. Like I said, I'm about

27:17.269 --> 27:19.036
to go on tour, and you...

27:19.071 --> 27:21.806
your schedule's crazy,
and it's just gonna get worse.

27:21.840 --> 27:24.742
So, what's the point
of having a dog, even one

27:24.776 --> 27:26.377
as cute as McConaughey,
if you can't

27:26.411 --> 27:29.580
take care of him,
and you can't enjoy him?

27:31.783 --> 27:33.951
You heard
what they do to the pets

27:33.985 --> 27:36.387
that you bring back
to the shelters, right?

27:36.421 --> 27:40.691
Well, then, you're gonna have
to find a home for him.

27:40.726 --> 27:42.259
And I promise you, some day,

27:42.294 --> 27:44.328
we're gonna have
everything that you want.

27:44.362 --> 27:45.963
Okay, and that includes a dog.

27:45.997 --> 27:48.566
But we're still figuring
things out between you and me,

27:48.600 --> 27:50.968
like who we are together
and where we're gonna be.

27:51.002 --> 27:53.471
I just don't think

27:53.505 --> 27:56.140
that we should drag McConaughey
into that, do you?

28:12.734 --> 28:14.701
Liz, send in my 10:00.

28:18.673 --> 28:21.809
Hi. Um, I'm Kurt Hummel.

28:21.843 --> 28:24.278
Um, I-I didn't
actually cause

28:24.312 --> 28:26.380
a major chemical spill
in National Park.

28:26.414 --> 28:28.582
Uh, your receptionist said
that you were really busy,

28:28.616 --> 28:32.352
and that was the only way that I
could make an appointment, so...

28:32.387 --> 28:34.054
Oh. Uh...

28:34.088 --> 28:35.222
Liz, call security.

28:35.256 --> 28:37.057
Well...
They should only need one guy.

28:37.091 --> 28:38.659
No. It's-it's about your mother.

28:38.693 --> 28:40.093
I'm-I'm friends with her.

28:40.128 --> 28:44.698
Wait. Is this some kind of
Martha Raye-Mark Harris thing?

28:44.732 --> 28:46.733
'Cause she doesn't
have any money.

28:46.768 --> 28:49.937
No, no. We're performing
